  "title": "SAFETY COORDINATOR",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Perform construction site safety inspections. Coordinate and implement all workplace safety and health control programs.</p>\n<p>· Perform the full range of workplace safety &amp; health responsibilities</p>\n<p>· Liaise closely with Project Manager &amp; Site Staff on all safety &amp; health issues on site</p>\n<p>· Daily site safety inspection &amp; compilation of all relevant reports &amp; records</p>\n<p>· Prepare accident reporting &amp; investigations</p>\n<p>· Monitor all staff &amp; workers in compliance with site safety rules &amp; regulations</p>\n<p>· Provide advice and assist Project Managers in the development, implementation, review, and revision of health, safety, and environmental sections of the Project Execution Plan.</p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Recognized  Qualifications/Safety Officer  qualification</li>\n  <li>Minimize 2 years experience in the capacity of WSHO in the construction industry</li>\n  <li>Preferably to commence work immediately</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>A competitive remuneration package commensurate with qualifications will be offered.</strong></p>\n<p>Interested candidates are invited to apply via email with an updated resume, which should include current and expected salaries, date of availability, and a recent photograph in MS Word Format</p>\n<p>We regret that only short-listed candidates will be notified.<br>\n <strong>Thank you for applying.</strong></p>",
